ch general (b. 1769) *[[1817]] &ndash; [[William Bligh]], English admiral and politician, 4th [[Governor of New South Wales]] (b. 1745) *[[1837]] &ndash; [[Robert Nicoll]], Scottish poet (b.1814) *[[1842]] &ndash; [[Thomas Hamilton (writer)|Thomas Hamilton]], Scottish philosopher and author (b. 1789) *[[1874]] &ndash; [[Constantin von Tischendorf]], German theologian, scholar, and academic (b. 1815) *[[1879]] &ndash; [[Jón Sigurðsson]], Icelandic scholar and politician, 1st [[List of Speakers of the Parliament of Iceland|Speaker of the Parliament of Iceland]] (b. 1811) *[[1891]] &ndash; [[Arthur Blyth]], English-Australian politician, 9th [[Premier of South Australia]] (b. 1823) *[[1894]] &ndash; [[Ferdinand de Lesseps]], French businessman and diplomat, co-developed the [[Suez Canal]] (b. 1805) *[[1899]] &ndash; [[Juan Luna]], Filipino painter and sculptor (b. 1857) *[[1902]] &ndash; [[Thomas Nast]], German-American cartoonist (b. 1840) *[[1906]] &ndash; [[Élie Ducommun]], Swiss journalist and educator, [[Nobel Peace Prize|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1833) *[[1913]] &ndash; [[Luigi Oreglia di Santo Stefano]], Italian cardinal (b. 1828) *[[1917]] &ndash; [[Ludwig Minkus]], Austrian violinist and composer (b. 1826) *[[1918]] &ndash; [[Frank Wilson (politician)|Frank Wilson]], English-Australian politician, 9th [[Premier of Western Australia]] (b. 1859) *[[1941]] &ndash; [[Attack on Pearl Harbor]]: ** [[Mervyn S. Bennion]], American captain (b. 1887) ** [[Frederick Curtice Davis]], American sailor (b. 1915) ** [[Julius Ellsberry]], American sailor (b. 1921) ** [[John C. England]], American sailor (b. 1920) ** [[Edwin J. Hill]], American sailor (b. 1894) ** [[Ralph Hollis]], American sailor (b. 1906) ** [[Herbert C. Jones]], American sailor (b. 1918) ** [[Isaac C. Kidd]], American admiral (b. 1884) ** [[Robert Lawrence Leopold]], American sailor (b. 1916) ** [[Herbert Hugo Menges]], American sailor (b. 1917) ** [[Thomas James Reeves]], American sailor (b. 1895) ** [[Alo